comment: I have never hit a woman in my life.  I was married to a woman who was mentally afflicted by childhood sexual abuses.  Justifiably affected of course.  During our years together, I attempted to help her by providing counselling, which she was VERY averse to.  She found it difficult to complete more than 1, 2. or 3 sessions with any Psychiatrist.  I had known and learned about her horrible experiences as a child; revealed to me from our first night together as Man and Woman and for years afterwards. She was absolutely beautiful, at one time modelled wedding dresses. She was  6 Foot tall and very fit. I would, at worse, try and hold her wrists.  On more than one occasion she held me down and would "knee me in the chest, breaking ribs.  Typically, I would tell the Physician " I fell ".  Her rage was startling; even to me. We separated until or if she would agree to a full course of counselling.  She finally did. She agreed, gently. to return for counselling one evening.  One week later she was dead.  Drinking and driving.   She could be as sweet a Lady as one could wish for.  She could be as vicious and cruel as a nightmare.  She was Educated, and could be great fun and bring an abundance of Joy into my life. I waited until I was in my mid-thirties to Marry however, I will never Marry again.  The point is that Men are usually viewed as the physical aggressor, by the public, the courts and even Family.  It was a tragedy and such a waste of a beautiful person who had the world at her feet.  It ended primarily due to the actions of some pedophile and a refusal to  accept the help of mental health professionals.  Utterly sad....

comment: I think if we look at this in reality and honestly we could say there are at least two sides to this airing of personal lives.  Of course , if you are successful as an actor and portraying a vision of yourself and others in the eye of a camera to be viewed by starstruck people, you are going to portray yourself as well as you can. Look at the situation. AH was willing to be involved with this man and did not concern herself with his marriage or his children..... red flag! But in the other hand JD chose to dissolve his relationship with his family .... for what? A new pretty face and a new piece of ... well you know..... red flag!  Actors are in the spotlight, no way around it. The reality is that all humans make choices and alit of those choices are bad.  I don‚Äôt have enough reliable information to judge this scenario.  I do however believe their is no innocent party here.... except maybe his children. Drugs , alcohol, fame and bad choices .... what could either of them expect the outcome to be? There are no fairytales even if you are in Hollywood.  Maybe we should just examine our own lives and not try to live in someone else‚Äôs fantasy world.  They are people and people mess up!  Take care of your own self  and your family.

As a First Nation Canadian mother, I myself stay hopeful... I advocate from a family level. And I under took the psychological changes that I needed, in order to thrive. I see the adversity firsthand against my children. And my reasoning for not conforming to unhealthy people, is commonly despised. Thankfully, for myself, I grew up with a sense of reasoning compassion and wisdom for right and wrong. Where, I have been able to seemingly avoid direct dysfunctions and keep a clear perspective about truth.
In contrast to this however, I do in fact suffer immensely with isolation effects. I dont have very severe symptoms of doubt. comment:
0:01- The smirk, duper‚Äôs delight, she‚Äôs enjoying the memory of doing this. She never answered the question bc she is lying. The entire dep is BS. I cant even watch her anymore, she triggers my ptsd. Her recording him in the kitchen is vile and incredibly an abusers doing. What this girl does not realize is that real victims would never act like this, specially in a deposition. I understand people are different, so i will speak for myself here, but when uve been beaten down, shamed, wrongly accused of cheating and dehumanized to every bad name under the sun by an abuser, and u fear for ur life, your demeanor is absolutely the opposite of this. I had the misfortune of going thru an abusive relationship with my ex and the last thing I wanted to do was perpetuate any more heat towards this person. I lost weight, my hair fell off, i was always bruised everywhere, couldn‚Äôt eat, couldn‚Äôt sleep, couldn‚Äôt look at anyone in the eye or speak to anyone without feeling i was doing something wrong, bc this person would accuse me of sleeping with everyone so in began behaving very introvertly to not upset him. Neither my friends nor family knew what was going on, i became isolated, depressed, a complete mess, a zombie, someone completely different, and was extremely upset and nervous about reliving these awful moments, so talking to the cops was very difficult. I didn‚Äôt even want to get this person arrested the last time he hurt me bc I was incapable of speaking up, but i knew at that point it was the right thing to do. After his arrest, I was advised to file an RO and when I went to do it, I couldn‚Äôt even get myself to finish filing it nor did i cont with the DV charges against him by the DA bc of fear of retaliation. I wanted to b done with this so badly, I moved out of state and left the past behind. This is how much fear I had. 

Eating in a deposition? Smiling? Are u serious? I was never EVER hungry or capable of speaking confidently about the events, let alone smile or enjoy that i was putting this person out in the open. Ive observed this demeanor in JD, so it is clear to me that AH is the one perpetuating this abuse on him. AH looks like shes making this up as she goes along. When uve been screamed at, pushed, hit, thrown down, you know exactly how it looks like, exactly how it feels on your body and cringe at the memory as it hurts so deeply to relieve it bc its a person you once truly loved. AH does not show a sliver of torment or sadness having to tell these events, she is enjoying every bit of her lie and deception to manipulate and bring JD down.This is not the demeanor of a victim. Her behavior from the events leading up to this, calling her publicist, demanding rhe money/penthouses/allowance, laughing in the kitchen recording, fighting with him in the videos and taunting him by calling him a baby bc he always runs away, seriously? This is someone who is manipulative, vindictive and abusive with a retaliation agenda. She has never feared for her life. She is not the victim here period. 

I do commend the REAL men and women survivors who are brave to come forward and get through the painful experience of facing their abuser and proceed with the full legal process; something i was too scared to do. But this case and her accusations, plus her duper‚Äôs delight in so many interviews, specifically when asked about punching JD and when asked about the 7 mill in that other panel, which shows she has always been out for blood. And although it is evident the relationship was toxic for years and became abusive, i believe AH planned to convince him to marry, to then execute the elaborate hoax against him. I believe she was and still is the abuser and JD is the victim of her doing.

comment:
Victims often do not do a very good job once they finally begin to record the aggressive partner parent or abuser in general.

It can be very nerve racking when fear is already present. 
It is proven that narcissists can be very dangerous.

However it is often very good thing for a victim to record a situation with an abuser for many reasons one of them being private reflection.

When a victim is finally able to play back an incident in private to themselve it helps them realize that the other person has become truly dangerous. 

It helps them to see the situation more clearly, there by they gain more courage to begin real change. 

It is factual that rarely if ever will an aggressor show the outside world that side of their personality sadly it is only let loose on their victim who experiences it in private.

More victims should record. It can help bring light to a victim and end a terrible spiral it may also be of importance to a law suit if needed.

comment:
I watched this and this seems like a woman who is at first thoroughly pissed and cannot contain herself when she is asked if she hit Johnny Depp, which is in line with her being the victim of domestic abuse and talking against it. Her behaviour is that of someone who's heart is racing and she's trying to convince people of the truth. And panicking about what if no one believes her. 

I've been in a situation like this and I identify every emotion. If you've faced a terrible crime that has destroyed a part of you and someone is claiming that you're lying and the actual abuser. You don't function like you normally do. The sarcastic smile of hate and disbelief. Your heart racing and you try to keep yourself contained so you don't appear hysterical even though you feel like it. Nothing feels the same in your body and everything feels forced and you just want to cry. This is why it seems that a successful Hollywood actor seemingly "can't act". If she was the ice cold manipulator everyone make her out to be, she would have a performance ready. 

I think big part what makes me believe Depp was the main abuser is his problems with drugs and alcohol, which is very common in family violence. Depp isn't bad but it's obvious his addictions have changed him recently. He isn't really the same as before it seems. Tell me Depp doesn't have a problem with drugs and alcohol?

But also we have to remember that we don't know the truth. I think my evidence is way larger than this whole comment section and try to convince me otherwise. But I can't say that I know what happened. So more than anything neither can you. So just away from this.

comment:
Many men fail to come forward when in a violent relationship. Unfortunately my skn in law was one/failing to warn us what my step daughter got up to when drunk.She has been an alcoholic for many years. Finally he moved his two young sons & himself out of the family home. My step daughter went ballistic. Got drunk. And I watched her grab the bathroom door and smashed it into her face. This culminated in two black eyes & a broken nose. Thinking she'd calm down.go home. SOBER UP..I was horrified when our son in law rang to say she'd been at his new "Safe House' looking battered & screaming 'YOU HIT ME!' Which had neighbours opening their doors & someone called the Police.
The Police turned up & arrested my son in law. Had he not been able to phone us he would have had a domestic violence placed on him & lost both the children to Social Services. As it happens the Police referred it as a 'Tit for Tat situation as their were NO witnesses! Only neighbours statements of 'yelling'.
THIS IS HOW EASY it is to end up looking battered & bruised as Amber Heard was photographed. Personally.i would SWEAR that woman slammed a door in her own face in a RAGE to bring Jonny Depp down!
For that reason I never saw Aquaman or anything else she has been in. And certainly WOULDNT be renting Aquamann 2 or The Mirror or ANYTHING starring Amber Heard!
SHE'S A FRAUD!
Today I still hope men STEP FORWARD & admit they are being battered by the women in their lives. For this reason alone Jonny Depp would end up being an advocate to STOP FEMALE ON MALE ABUSE.
Thank you for reading my story.And JONNY..GOOD LUCK!

comment:
I know this is old,
 August 13th 2016 AH v JD Divorce Settlement hearing.
Partial transcript of the incident on the stairs involving Whitney Heard 
I think I have found something that perhaps has been overlooked in her oral evidence. Her counsel and Amber made such a spectacle out of the cross examination by Ms Wass for JD it is very easy to overlook the obvious misinformation coming from AH.
I was watching her body language which was full of flaws in itself and the evidence should have been disregarded on that alone.
If you listen to her oral evidence she totally stuffs it up. 
I will break this down, shorten it and leave out AH's ramblings so,
Let's look at the involvement of Whitney in one of her fights with JD.
Ms Wass counsel for JD:
"Have you ever hit Johnny Depp with a closed fist?"
(wanting a yes or no answer)
After a chunk of chocolate and a very long pause.......... we end up with the 
"Incident on the stairs" (including her sister Whitney)
Ms Wass had 3 attempts at getting a yes no answer but was getting nowhere due to chocolate consumption on the stand by Amber and constant interjections from her counsel.
Transcript:
Amber: " One time JD hit me hard and repeatedly, I screamed for Security" 
(JD's Security now on scene) 
Amber: "Jerry or Sean does nothing" One of them says "Boss"
Heard & JD are on the landing of the stairs arguing.
Amber: "My sister RUNS DOWN THE STAIRS"
Ms Wass: "Did you hit JD?"
Interjection by AH's counsel 
(trying to save AH)
Judge dismisses interjection
Amber: "He was attempting to push my sister down the stairs" (note Amber said Whitney had already run down the stairs)
I have shortened this up and left some of it out which you can read in the transcripts.
Further on.....
Amber: "I don't know what I did but I know I jumped in between the action" (wasn't Amber in the action already? It wasn't a fight between JD & Whitney was it?)
Amber: "She (Whitney) was standing at the TOP of the stairs" 
(Did Amber see her run up the stairs now?)
Further on.. (with no other real evidence or facts in her evidence except a lot of hand motions and pretence)
Amber: "I saw her (Whitney) SITTING on top of a flight of stairs and she has never hurt anyone in her life and does not deserve to be pushed down a flight of stairs"
Ok, so first:
Whitney ran down the stairs.
AH and JD are on the landing of the stairs arguing.
AH: "Whitney was attempting to break us up" which would mean that Whitney was on the landing now with AH & JD Amber: When he laid his hands on her "I jumped in between the action that I saw could lead to a fatal injury to my sister, she was STANDING at the TOP of a flight of stairs and she has never hurt anyone in her life"
Amber: "I acted defensively in her life. I saw her SITTING on top of a flight of stairs
( From Standing at the top of a flight of stairs Amber now sees her SITTING at the top of the stairs away from JD who was going to push her down the stairs. (from the landing?)
He hasn't moved from the landing.
OMG! If this isn't a fabrication of what transpired I don't know what is!

comment:
Well, this is much easier to say it on the internet and I know I definitely wouldn't talk about this in real life, but I want to show my support to JD with my story. 

I have been abused by my dad's new girlfriend years ago. She was extremely manipulative, violent and insane when he wasn't around, and she almost sent him to jail because she made him absolutely crazy. So he slapped her, like anyone would in front of such a disgusting person. (and that's all)
Right after abusing me and forcing me to tell the police my dad is a rapist, she started to continue her business on him to make him feel guilty. She was also a pathological liar, she never admitted anything wrong she could do. But she had an excuse, because she is a woman.

And finally, he lost the "fight". 
One of the sweetest men has been considered as a rapist, but I'm the only one who knows what really happened because I was there. 
I listened to everything in the staircase, and she tried to make me shut up when she knew about it, because I witnessed what she did. 

Luckily, my family on my mother's side believed me and cancelled her (we are really close to each other and they are great people, really) and they knew she wasn't a good person at all inside anyways. She also had an abusive and violent daughter who personally ruined my life during years, pushing me to kill myself with a huge mental abuse, she lived in the same house as me. You know, I was a 13 years-old boy when this shit happened. A boy, and she never got grounded because she is a girl. 

The police didn't believe us, my family and I. And now they remember my dad as a women abuser, with a weak son that can't even defend himself because "he is a man".

But, you know, it's hard to defend ourselves against narcissic people because the ones who loves them always find an excuse, or people defend them because of their gender.

And that's how the good ones fall for stupied lies and money stories. 

Everything in Amber is fake, and everybody knows it. For us, it's like JD won.

comment:
No one believed that OJ beat Nicole in the beginning.  OJ was a sports legend, he had a successful television and movie career, he had looks, he. Had money, he had charisma and he worked for charities.  You all know the litany.  You all know what he presented to the world.  But the fact remains that cops would be called for a domestic and would show up to the scene at OJ's house.  There was evidence of some type of altercation, but once they saw it was OJ, and he turned on the OJ good old boy charm, they would call it a day.  Like Amber, Nicole had to document the abuse  because she knew that she was swimming upstream when it came to getting someone to actually listen to her claims.  Her sister helped her to document the abuse by taking pictures, or she would stand at the bathroom mirror and do it herself.  She put the pictures in a safe deposit box. Clearly that wasn't enough to help her go up against "monster" OJ.  We posthumously saw the photo evidence of the abuse she endured when OJ raged on her.  
OJ knew that he was a media darling,  He would tell Nicole that he could kill her and get away with it just to taunt and torture her emotionally.  Bits of that relationship ring true for me in this case.  That is why I think that the majority of the public is getting this wrong.  Was Johnny and Amber's relationship effed up on two sides.  Yes.  But my gut has been telling me for a few years that there is something very wrong with Depp and the way in which he handles adversity and stress.  And like OJ, he knows how to turn on the charm when in a tight spot.  Like the time he showed up at a late night tv interview with a bandaged hand.  He said something about an accident while driving a go cart, or something similar to that.  Almost made light of it.  Somebody later said that Johnny had actually damaged his hand when he punched a mirror while in a rage.  It's been a couple of years, perhaps more, but as I watch the video of Johnny being "monster" Johnny it all falls into place, what was said about how he really received his hand injury.
More simply stated, I don't call BS on Amber's claims of abuse.

comment: The ignorance at play in the media is exceptionally concerning. Documenting abuse is the official advice from all domestic abuse experts and resources. Sometimes it's the only way a victim can prove the abuse, especially if the perpetrator is a malignant narcissist/pyschopath/Anti social personality disordered etc. The manipulation these personalities are capable of is terrifying. They can go from raging at their victim to politely offering a police officer a cup of tea at the door. Another aspect of this is "reactionary abuse," which is again a well known dynamic in an abusive relationship. The victim is trying to survive and that, combined with the severe mental brainwashing (peptide addiction) which wears away at their psyche can lead them to finally lash out in response to the daily torture of manipulation, gaslighting and basically never ever feeling safe. They also know instinctively that should they leave the relationship this will be the most dangerous time. Another well known abuse statistic is that the most dangerous time for a victim is just after exiting, when the abuser has lost control of the carefully constructed abuse dynamic they've been building up a fostering. Why doesn't the media understand these Domestic Abuse concepts? It all seems to be presented with an air of "who knows" and "no one can work it out." I can promise you that a narcissistic abuse expert or specialist psychologist in Cluster B personality disorders would be able to shed light on this in minutes - why is this insight not being included in reporting? I believe Amber Heard is the victim - she made a motivational support video for victims, using her experience to help them and that is something that a narcissist or psychopath would not be inclined to do as so much of the abuse relies on a veil of secrecy with one image presented to the public and another behind closed doors. She is being re-victimised, re-traumatised and re-abused by this widespread show of ignorance about Domestic Abuse in the media.

comment: How does one have the presence of mind during a violent altercation to film it?  I have to out myself to an extent here as someone who has been abusive to my partner in the beginning of our relationship.  I have BPD and have difficulty controlling my anger.  Thankfully I have engaged in a lot of therapy and with the love and support of my boyfriend have managed to overcome my propensity for violence.  Anyway, back then, once the dust settled we would talk and try to understand what had happened.  I desperately wanted to be able to work out what was triggering the extreme anger in me and we often discussed trying to film the fights so that I could look back and see exactly what was going on.  We were never, ever able to do it because you just don‚Äôt have the time to think when it‚Äôs happening.  You‚Äôd have to either know in advance that a fight was going to happen or you‚Äôd need to halt it midway through, which is just impossible.  The entire interaction in the kitchen clip just seems so calculated.  Given that I actively wanted to film my own outbursts but was never able to do it, and neither was my boyfriend, it is baffling to me that this was documented the way it was. My partner says that he was never scared of me in a physical sense and he doesn‚Äôt consider himself to have been abused (and that‚Äôs just us.  By definition I would say that he probably was abused by me) but even so, during a fight he would be way too busy trying to manage the situation to even think about getting his phone out, and he certainly would have been worried about making things worse if he did. If she was so abused by him I can‚Äôt see any way that she would feel comfortable taking the risk of filming him.  It‚Äôs very odd.

comment:
‚ÄòConcierge manager Trinity Esparza said she saw no injuries to Miss Heard's face after Depp allegedly threw a mobile phone at her 'like a baseball pitcher' during a blazing row on May 21, 2016.

Miss Esparza, who owned the concierge company at the exclusive Eastern Columbia Building, said she saw Miss Heard almost every day throughout the week after the alleged phone-hurling assault and the actress bore 'a clear, and unmarked face'.

On May 25, Miss Esparza said she even complimented Miss Heard by saying her 'skin looks flawless' and asked what moisturiser she used. 

Then, on May 27 - six days after the alleged attack by Depp - she saw Miss Heard with 'a red mark underneath her right eye' and 'a sad look on her face'.

Upon then reviewing security footage, beginning on May 21, she 'saw Miss Heard on a multitude of security camera footage clips, on each day of the ensuing week'. 

She added: 'I was able to zoom in on Miss Heard's face in order to view the footage in greater detail. I did not see any bruises, cuts, swelling, red marks or any other injuries of any kind.' 

Miss Esparza alleges that a few weeks later - June or early July - she saw Elon Musk who came down to the reception around 9am 'and looked like he had just woken up with messy hair'. 

She says her concierge colleague told her Mr Musk had been visiting Miss Heard late at night for more than a year, when Depp was away filming.

Then on the SAME day as she saw Mr Musk, Miss Heard later came down, and had 'three small round bruises on her neck and two Band-Aids on her arm', plus 'a faint mark on her left cheek, below the eye'.
WEEKS after Johnny had left.

Hmm ü§î

comment: I watch blow-by-blow of this case by lawyers and legal professionals. Everything I see by so-called mainstream commentators is heavily biased toward Amber. I get it. I do. Men do get violently assaulted by women, and get laughed at when they come forward, and arrested if they try to defend themselves. It's a fact. I am a strong advocate against domestic violence of ANY kind. And it's a fact that most known and proven victims are women, who are also often not taken seriously. comment:
It is very.... disagreeable when one spouse abuses the other, no matter what the provocation, and doubly so when one spouse is seen as being in the "dominant" position in a relationship simply due to the happenstances of their gender at birth and is thus perceived as being the abuser, rather than the victim.   We, as a society have become too, overly-attuned to the thought that men are naturally in a superior position over women due in large to how patriarchal our society still is, even is this age of supposed equality between sexes, that we have become used to accepting that this is how its always suppose to be. And with the far too numerous cases in the news in recent years of men abusing their female partners, we have become conditioned to the idea that it could not possibly be any other way. So when a case comes along where it appears that yet-another-man has apparently abused his partner, we naturally react with shaming for the male partner and comforting for the female partner. We have become too conditioned to this now-reflex motion to be able to accept that sometimes, its the female who is the abuser and the male who is the victim. And its in this manner that lets people like Amber Heard step forward and publicly accuse her spouse Johnny Depp of being yet-another of these spousal-abusing monsters, with her knowing full-well that society-at-large will reflexively side with her, especially if she simply "acts" like the abused spouse. She knows that public opinion will automatically crucify her spouse, no matter what the ultimate outcome is for her, even if she is found out in the end, and so, she has nothing to really lose in the end, or so she hopes.

Spousal abuse is a horrible thing that no person should ever have to suffer through, and while its comforting to know that society-at-large is willing to step forth and help comfort and console those who have gone through this, while at the same time punishing those who would inflict such on the abused spouse, I can only hope that the same will hold true when the abuser turns out to be a woman and the abused spouse turns out to be a man. There shouldn't be a double-standard here where spousal abuse is involved, simply because of the circumstances of one's gender at birth, nor because of what the "historical statistics" state is "the norm" in these cases. Let's do the right thing here people.ü•∫ üò© üòî
